Title: Lucky Cat Shower Curtain
Body (HTML):
The maneki-neko, which literally translates to "beckoning cat," but is more commonly known as the lucky cat is a common Japanese good luck charm. The figurine is usually made of ceramic in modern times and is often believed to bring good luck to the owner. These calico Japanese Bobtails are often displayed in shops and other business to bring prosperity, but you can get our all over print Lucky Cat Shower Curtain and take good fortune with you, even in the bath! Title: Om Namah Shivaya Shower Curtain
Body (HTML):
The Om Namah Shivaya Shower Curtain is named after a salutation to the Divine. According to Hindu traditions, the human body is made up of five natural elements and these holy letters represent these elements. Shiv Panchakshari Mantra is said to have evolved from the five seeds of aforesaid natural elements.

Om' purifies Bramhatatva and Crown Chakra

Na energizes the Prithvi Tatva (Earth element)

Ma energizes the Jal Tatva (Water factor)

Shi energizes Agni Tatva (Fire element)

Va energizes Vayu Tatva (Air factor) and

Ya energizes Akash Tatva (Sky element).

Plus it's Rad as Fu!
